# Feature Sliced Design (FSD)

## Layers

From top to bottom (higher layers import from lower ones, never the reverse):

`app` > `pages` > `widgets` > `features` > `entities` > `shared`

- **app** — entry point, providers, router, store composition, global styles
- **pages** — route-level components; compose widgets, features, and entities
- **widgets** — large self-contained UI blocks assembled from features/entities
- **features** — user interactions with business logic (forms, toggles, actions)
- **entities** — domain models (user, product) with their UI, model, and API
- **shared** — reusable utilities, UI kit, API client; zero business logic

## Import Rules

A module may only import from layers **strictly below** it. Cross-imports between slices on the same layer are forbidden.

```typescript
// GOOD — page imports from features and shared
import { LoginForm } from "@/features/auth";
import { cn } from "@/shared/lib";

// BAD — feature imports from a page (upward)
import { HomePage } from "@/pages/home";

// BAD — one entity imports from another entity (same layer)
import { UserCard } from "@/entities/user";  // inside entities/post
```

## Slice Structure

Each slice contains segments and a barrel export:

```
src/<layer>/<slice>/
  ui/          — components + colocated .scss
  model/       — Redux slices, selectors, types
  api/         — API calls (RTK Query or thunks)
  lib/         — helpers scoped to this slice
  index.ts     — public API (barrel export)
```

Not every segment is required — include only what the slice needs.

## Public API

Every slice **must** have an `index.ts` that re-exports only its public interface. Import from the barrel, never from internal paths.

```typescript
// GOOD
import { HomePage } from "@/pages/home";

// BAD — reaches into internal segment
import { HomePage } from "@/pages/home/ui/HomePage";
```

## Project Conventions

- **Path alias**: `@/*` maps to `src/*`
- **Styling**: BEM via `cn` from `@/shared/lib` (wraps `bem-cn-lite`); colocate `.scss` files next to their component
- **State**: Redux Toolkit slices live in `model/` segments; compose reducers in `src/app/store.ts`
- **Routing**: React Router configuration lives in `src/app/router.tsx`
